possible to define the correspondence via facts for `file_alias/2' in
a file declared with `multifile:alias_file/1' in the program: those
facts will be dynamically loaded when running the program.
Alternatively, the correspondence can be defined via shell
environment variables, by defining the value of a variable by the
(symbolic) name of the file to be the path of the actual file.

