92.2.2 Specifying Paths
-----------------------

Using the `vpath/1' predicate it is possible in configuration files
to define several paths in which files related to the rules can be
located. In this way, not all files need to be in the same directory
as the configuration file. For example:

     :- use_package(fsyntax).

     vpath := '/home/clip/Systems/ciao/lib'.
     vpath := '/home/clip/Systems/ciao/library'.
     vpath := '/home/clip/Systems/lpdoc/lib'.


