205 Underlying data-storage module
**********************************

*Author(s):* Arsen Kostenko.

   This module contains very low-level utilities of data storage
specific to a single node. Neither data sharing nor remote invocation
is performed at this level. Note that no dedicated data manipulation
is performed neither on this level. Also keep in mind that concept of
`Key' should always meet the same constraints as the second argument
of `functor/3' predicate. Important decision taken at this point is
representation of all information stored in the DHT as usual Prolog
facts. This behavior is implemented by representing relations of form
`Key' -> `Value' in form of `Key'(`Value') facts.

